'From Squeak3.6beta of ''4 July 2003'' [latest update: #5419] on 11 September 2003 at 12:39:56 am'!"Change Set:		5420advanceToGammaOr37-dewDate:			11 September 2003Author:			Doug WayThis is the last update for version 3.6beta.  In its postscript is an executable statement that will set the version forward to either 3.6gamma or 3.7alpha, at user option."!"Postscript:Offer the chance to advance the version number."(self confirm: 'There are no further updates for Squeak 3.6beta.Do you wish to advance to version 3.7alpha?[Yes] Your system will be marked as 3.7alpha, and you willsubsequently receive ''test pilot'' updates for 3.7.[No] Your system will be marked as 3.6gamma, allowing youto receive only final fixes for the 3.6 stable release.[Neither] You may choose No, and immediately quit without saving,allowing you to make a backup copy before adopting this change.DO YOU WANT TO ADVANCE to Version 3.7alpha now?')	ifTrue: [SystemVersion newVersion: 'Squeak3.7alpha'.			SystemVersion current date: '11 September 2003'.			self inform: 'You may now save this Version 3.7alpha imageand retrieve updates again for 3.7alpha and beyond.']	ifFalse: [SystemVersion current version: 'Squeak3.6gamma'; date: '11 September 2003'.			self inform: 'You may now save this Version 3.6gamma imageand retrieve updates again for any final fixes to 3.6.- - - - -(If you quit without saving now, your image will revert to3.6beta without any of the updates you just loaded)'].!